asty of goblin kings in Permafrost, how the heck did a goblin get a royal name? How the heck did 4 of them survive? This Thex is completely expendable, I kill him on sight.)<br><br>Princess Lenya Thex (In Felwithe, I hear she's fishy, but cannot confirm, because I don't want to.)<br><br>King Tearis Thex (High Elf King of Felwithe, I might even say King of Faydwer if I were drunk enough. An arrogant hothead, he sliced Danak's head off before the Iksar could confess. Go figure, High Elves aren't so great at espionage either.. Now, I haven't actually &quot;met&quot; this king, but I have heard him shout across the Faydark.)<br><br>So, who care's about &quot;Thex&quot;? I have a theory that &quot;thex&quot; simply is a surname that means &quot;royal&quot; or &quot;king&quot;. Perhaps this is a carry-over from the Combine Empire? Else, how do we explain a butt-bearing Goblin in this mix? Thex must lead to something grand..<br><br>Any thoughts?<br><br><br><br>Next week, let's talk about Miragul <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>regards, <br>Loristatt<br><br> <p><img src="http://207.176.26.33/~loristatt/loribanner.jpg"><br><Center>FINIS PER SOMNIVM REPERIO TIBISACRA COR VENEFICVS OSTIVM AVRVM "Comes the end by sleep, I will reparefor you the Sacred Heart which is magic that opens upon the Altar."</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utaurusl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaurusL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(11/25/01 8:08:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons